              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>3</fr:month>
              <fr:day>10</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0009/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>gtop-0009</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/gtop-0009/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Metric Space">Metric Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
A <html:strong>metric space</html:strong> is an ordered pair <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(M,d)]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is a set and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> is a <html:strong>metric</html:strong> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>, i.e., a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d:M\times  M \to  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> satisfying the following axioms for all points <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y,z \in  M]]></fr:tex>:
</html:p>
            <html:ul><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,x) = 0]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\text {If } x\neq  y,\text { then } d(x,y)>0]]></fr:tex>. (Positivity)</html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y) = d(y,x)]]></fr:tex>. (Symmetry)</html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,z) \leq  d(x,y) + d(y,z)]]></fr:tex>. (Triangle inequality)</html:li></html:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>3</fr:month>
              <fr:day>7</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0008/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>gtop-0008</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/gtop-0008/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Compactness">Compactness</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
    A <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topological space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, \tau )]]></fr:tex> is <html:strong>compact</html:strong> if every <fr:link href="/gtop-0007/" title="Open Cover" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0007/" display-uri="gtop-0007" type="local">open cover</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> has a <fr:link href="/gtop-0007/" title="Open Cover" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0007/" display-uri="gtop-0007" type="local">finite subcover</fr:link>.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
    A subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \subseteq  X]]></fr:tex> is compact if it is compact as a topological space with the subspace topology, or equivalently, if every open cover of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> by open sets in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> has a finite subcover.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
    In <fr:link href="/gtop-0004/" title="Euclidean Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0004/" display-uri="gtop-0004" type="local">Euclidean space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex>, the Heine-Borel theorem gives a concrete characterization: a subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \subseteq  \mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex> is compact if and only if it is <fr:link href="/gtop-0006/" title="Closed Set" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0006/" display-uri="gtop-0006" type="local">closed</fr:link> and bounded (i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \subseteq  B(0, R)]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R > 0]]></fr:tex>).
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
